dataset_fields.label: Description
dataset_fields.form_placeholder: eg. Some useful notes about the data
dataset_fields.help_text: Descriptive information about the dataset. Can also include further information or caveats pertaining to the data.

dataset_fields.label: Access Level
dataset_fields.help_text: Provide an access level label for your dataset. These will appear on your dataset to give users an indication of data availability. This doesn't affect access to your data - you'll still need to secure individual resources if required.

choices_placeholder_text.open_login:
This dataset has been classified as Open - Login by the data publisher. A specific Data Access Statement has not been supplied. Typically, logging in is required for reporting and tracking purposes.

Open - Login datasets are available for use by everyone but require logging in. For datasets in the Shared Land Information Platform (SLIP), you’ll need to register a SLIP login.

Use of this data may be subject to licence restrictions - be sure to read the licence information provided above.
choices_placeholder_text.fees_apply:
This dataset has been classified as Fees Apply by the data publisher. A specific Data Access Statement has not been supplied. Typically, fees are managed by the organisation publishing the data.

Fees Apply datasets are generally available for use by everyone but require payment of a regular or once-off fee. Contact the data publisher via the Request Access button to enquire about access and fees.

Use of this data may be subject to licence restrictions - be sure to check the Licence information above.
choices_placeholder_text.restricted:
This dataset has been classified as Restricted by the data publisher. A specific Data Access Statement has not been supplied. Typically, restricted data is sensitive in some way.

You’ll need approval from the data publisher to access a Restricted dataset. Contact the data publisher via the Request Access button to enquire about access.

Use of this data may be subject to licence restrictions - be sure to check the Licence information above.
choices_placeholder_text.govt_only:
This dataset has been classified as Government Use Only by the data publisher. A specific Data Access Statement has not been supplied. Typically, data that’s restricted to government users is sensitive in some way. Data may be restricted to specific government organisations or certain levels of government (such as WA state government).

Government Use Only datasets are generally accessed through the Shared Land Information Platform (SLIP). If your organisation is authorised to access this dataset, you’ll need to register a SLIP login and join your organisation’s group. If your organisation is not authorised to access this dataset and you would like to enquire about alternatives, contact the data publisher via the Request Access button.

Use of this data may be subject to licence restrictions - be sure to check the Licence information above.
choices_placeholder_text.mixed:
This dataset has been classified as Mixed Access by the data publisher. A specific Data Access Statement has not been supplied. Typically, Mixed Access datasets are available as a variety of resources, with some types of resources being more sensitive than others.

Check the access level of the resource you require. If the resource is not Open or Open - Login, you’ll need to contact the data publisher via the Request Access button to enquire about access.

Use of this data may be subject to licence restrictions - be sure to check the Licence information above.

dataset_fields.label: Data Access Statement
dataset_fields.help_text: A brief statement clarifying access and use of this dataset. Default text will be used if you don’t supply your own, but it’s recommended that you provide specific statements for all datasets with an access level of "Open - Login" and lower. You can find the default access statements on the Data Toolkit - these may also be helpful for writing your own.
dataset_fields.form_placeholder:
A good data access statement should include the following:

- Clarification of the access level. e.g. Government Use Only: This dataset has been made available to [x], [y] and [z] agencies.
- Reasons for any restrictions. e.g. Open - Login: This data is only available to registered users because [organisation] is required by legislation to track usage.
- Any conditions of use you’d like to highlight, and/or reminding users to check the licence information.
- How to apply for or enquire about access.

dataset_fields.label: Request Access URL
dataset_fields.help_text: If you want to direct users enquiring about access to a webform or other webpage, enter a URL for the "Request Access" button on your dataset. If you don't supply a URL, the button will direct users to email the dataset maintainer provided.

dataset_fields.label: Tags
dataset_fields.help_text: Some tags (or keywords) that describe your data.

dataset_fields.label: License
dataset_fields.help_text: Licenses for data.wa.gov.au (Licensing Creative Commons is endorsed by WA Government and the recommended default under the Open Data Policy)

dataset_fields.label: Custom License URL
dataset_fields.help_text: Enter the link to your custom licence. When users click on the licence information for your dataset, they'll be taken to this URL.

dataset_fields.label: Additional Licensing Options URL
dataset_fields.help_text: Enter the link to your additional licence options. An "Additonal licence options available" link will be added to your dataset's licence information.

dataset_fields.label: Data Portal
dataset_fields.help_text: Another website or resource that users may go to to discover more context and information about the dataset (e.g. The relevant page on your agency's website). If that does not apply, leave it blank.

dataset_fields.label: Data Homepage
dataset_fields.help_text: For datasets that exist in another catalogue this will be the access point for detailed catalogue-specific information about the dataset. If you're unsure, leave this blank.

dataset_fields.label: Author
dataset_fields.help_text: The name and email address of the person who is primarily responsible for creating and maintaining the data.

dataset_fields.label: Maintainer
dataset_fields.help_text: The name and email address of the person who is responsible for maintaining the dataset on data.wa.gov.au. The contact provided here will be used as the contact point for users who have questions about the dataset.

dataset_fields.label: Maintainer Email
dataset_fields.help_text: The name and email address of the person who is responsible for maintaining the dataset on data.wa.gov.au. The contact provided here will be used as the contact point for users who have questions about the dataset.

dataset_fields.label: Theme
dataset_fields.help_text: The AGIFT top level government function to which the dataset relates.

dataset_fields.label: Geospatial Theme
dataset_fields.help_text: A broad geographic data theme to assist in the organisation of geographic / location datasets. Where there are overlaps between categories, please select the most appropriate. The ANZLIC Open Spatial Data Topic Category Taxonomy is a high-level taxonomy based on the ISO 19115-1 Metadata Standard.

dataset_fields.label: Published on
dataset_fields.help_text: The date on which this dataset was, or shall be, published.

dataset_fields.label: Data last updated on
dataset_fields.help_text: The date on which the main data resource on data.wa.gov.au was last updated.

dataset_fields.label: Update Frequency
dataset_fields.help_text: How often the dataset is updated. Eg: Daily, Weekly, Never.

dataset_fields.label: Temporal coverage from
dataset_fields.help_text: The span of time from the data is applicable. If the data applies only to a single point in time you should only fill in the Temporal Coverage From field.

dataset_fields.label: Temporal coverage to
dataset_fields.help_text: The span of time to which the data is applicable. If the data applies only to a single point in time you should only fill in the Temporal Coverage From field.

dataset_fields.label: Digital Object Identifier
dataset_fields.help_text: The Digital Object Identifier assigned to your dataset (if you have created one). More information about the DOI system is available here, and is more typically used in scientific disciplines and publishing. If you're unsure, leave this blank.

dataset_fields.label: Citation
dataset_fields.help_text: The citation that users of the dataset should use in publications, articles, et cetera. If you're unsure, leave this blank.

dataset_fields.label: Geospatial Source Projection
dataset_fields.help_text: Geographic coordinate system and datum specification. For geospatial data only.

dataset_fields.label: Harvesting Source
dataset_fields.help_text: Geographic coordinate system and datum specification. For geospatial data only.

dataset_fields.label: Harvesting Service
dataset_fields.help_text: Where applicable, the service that this dataset was harvested from - typically a web service name. This metadata item supports DataWA data and metadata harvesters.

dataset_fields.label: Dataset Coverage
dataset_fields.help_text: Define the area covered by the records in the dataset by selecting from the pre-defined list, drawing on the map. Alternatively, provide a GeoJSON Polygon or MultiPolygon. (Note: Geospatial data hosted in SLIP will automatically populate this field.)

resource_fields.label: Name
resource_fields.form_placeholder: eg. Observations of X at Y

resource_fields.label: Description
resource_fields.form_placeholder: Some useful notes about the resource

resource_fields.label: Access Level
resource_fields.help_text: Provide an access level label for this resource. These will appear next to the resource to give users an indication of data availability. This doesn't affect access to the resource - you'll still need to secure access to the resource yourself.
